efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(1) average per operation
space complexity: O(N) where N is number of distinct keys
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a doubly-linked list of buckets (each holding a set of keys with the same count) plus a hash map from key to bucket. inc/dec adjust the bucket of a key in O(1) by moving it to an adjacent bucket or creating/removing buckets as needed; getMinKey/getMaxKey read the head/tail buckets in O(1).

